**Title from related Incident record IM2841636:
Outlook data recovery
Solution:
Related Incident IM2841636 closed.
Delta Air Lines users pretty much have access to their deleted items using Outlook Recover Deleted Items tool. Please note that Delta standard policy is email hygiene which is performed daily, which moves items older than 60 days. These items will be moved to purge, at which point, they remain for 7 days.

The only option available to restore e-mails is a feature on your outlook client named "Recover Deleted Items", If you do not find the messages under Recover Deleted Items means those messages were already purged from the Servers. Delta Policy is go to the tape in instance of catastrophic failure only.

This is the policy applied for all Delta's users and to not happen this again we recommend create PST files, store it on File Servers (HomeDrive) in order to save important e-mails. If you have any doubts or questions about how to do that Field Ops Team can assist you.

Since there is not action on your incident we are considering it as closed.

Title: Cannot Access Outlook
Description: Cannot Access Outlook
Solution:
Clear entries in Credential Manager
Go to Start, Control Panel, Credential manager, Windows Credentials, Generic Credentials. Remove the one that says Microsoft_OC1:uir=xxxxx

Remove Crypto Folder
Trunk into machine \\machinename\c$ - to go folder that is under C:\programdata\microsoft\crypto\RSA and find the one that says S-1-5 and rename it or delete it

Change the registry entry in for Communicator Save Password
Go to Registry Editor (Start > Run > regedit > OK)
Choose

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Communicator
Double-click the value SavePassword and set it to 0
Unlock users ID to make sure they are not locked, and then launch Lync

Solution:
Related Incident IM2877041 closed.
Here's what you need to do to fix it:

1. On the phone, open the E-Mail app
2. Hit the Menu Key > Settings > General Settings
3. Select Spam Addresses and look for any errant email addresses, especially *@yourdomain.com entries, which would filter any messages from your domain.
4. Remove those addresses

Now the user can move the messages out of the Unwanted Folder and delete that folder, and email will stop being filtered improperly.

**Title from related Incident record IM2901486:
outlook data recovery
Solution:
Related Incident IM2901486 closed.
Delta Air Lines users pretty much have access to their deleted items using Outlook Recover Deleted Items tool. Please note that Delta standard policy is email hygiene which is performed daily, which moves items older than 60 days. These items will be moved to purge, at which point, they remain for 7 days.

The only option available to restore e-mails is a feature on your outlook client named "Recover Deleted Items", If you do not find the messages under Recover Deleted Items means those messages were already purged from the Servers. Delta Policy is go to the tape in instance of catastrophic failure only.

This is the policy applied for all Delta's users and to not happen this again we recommend create PST files, store it on File Servers (HomeDrive) in order to save important e-mails. If you have any doubts or questions about how to do that Field Ops Team can assist you.

Since there is not action on your incident we are considering it as closed.

Name: LOURINDA HARRIS
Title: Keeps receiving pop on Outlook to login
Description: Keeps receiving pop on Outlook to login
Solution:
Clear entries in Credential Manager
Go to Start, Control Panel, Credential manager, Windows Credentials, Generic Credentials. Remove the one that says Microsoft_OC1:uir=xxxxx

Remove Crypto Folder
Trunk into machine \\machinename\c$ - to go folder that is under C:\programdata\microsoft\crypto\RSA and find the one that says S-1-5 and rename it or delete it

Change the registry entry in for Communicator Save Password
Go to Registry Editor (Start > Run > regedit > OK)
Choose

HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Communicator
Double-click the value SavePassword and set it to 0
Unlock users ID to make sure they are not locked, and then launch Lync

From	Subject	Received	Size	Categories

From: Bolden, Sandra

Subject: IM2966244-Outlook Indexing.


Good Morning Austin,


I have attached the steps for you to perform to assist you with your “Indexing” issue.
•	Go to File > Options
•	In Search settings, click Indexing Options…
•	Click Modify
•	Un-check Microsoft Outlook from the list of Indexed Locations
•	Close Outlook completely and check the Task Manager (ctrl+alt+del) to see if no Outlook processes are running
•	Find the location of your PST or OST files
o	Go to File > Account Settings > Account Settings
o	Click on the Data Files tab
o	Select your Outlook file from the list and click Open File Location…
•	Right click on the .pst or .ost file and click Properties
•	Click Advanced
•	Make sure that the box next to ‘Allow this file to have contents indexed in addition to file’ is checked.
•	Click OK
Follow the steps outlined in step 2. Make sure this time that the box next to Microsoft Outlook is checked.
Give Outlook a little time to check the state of the indexing. It may be that it needs to add new items to the index. After a few minutes, you can try searching again.
•	In Outlook 2013 click on the File tab, then click Options > Search
•	Click Indexing Options
•	You should now see what locations are being indexed. Click Advanced
•	Under Troubleshooting, click Rebuild
•	Rebuilding will take some time so make sure to leave your PC running for a while, preferably when you don’t need to work with it since indexing can impact the speed of your computer.
•	In Outlook 2013 click on the File tab, then click Options > Search
•	Click Indexing Options
•	You should now see what locations are being indexed. Click Advanced
•	Under Troubleshooting, click Rebuild
•	Rebuilding will take some time so make sure to leave your PC running for a while, preferably when you don’t need to work with it since indexing can impact the speed of your computer.
If you still can’t find the email you’re looking for, there may be a problem with your index. Rebuilding the index in Outlook 2013 isn’t too difficult, only time consuming. Here’s how to rebuild:
•	In Outlook 2013 click on the File tab, then click Options > Search
•	Click Indexing Options
•	You should now see what locations are being indexed. Click Advanced
•	Under Troubleshooting, click Rebuild
•	Rebuilding will take some time so make sure to leave your PC running for a while, preferably when you don’t need to work with it since indexing can impact the speed of your computer.

Title: outlook is auto sending meeting invites

outlook is auto sending meeting invites
cabin maintenance operations daily meeting

-it stopped sending them and today began sending out invites to canceled meetings
**Title from related Incident record IM2995842:
outlook is auto sending meeting invites
Solution:
Related Incident IM2995842 closed.
Emailed the below to user:

Hi Eri,

The Email Exchange Server Support team transferred your ticket to us to investigate the issue further. Unfortunately, this issue is actually a known issue with Apple ActiveSync in Outlook 2016. There have been vast numbers of people (consumers) complaining this very issue that you reported. There is not a solution that we can deploy or implement locally besides suggesting to you the below work-around to see if it will help. Internally, we have received many of this same issue before.

The issue could be related to someone in the distribution list accepted certain meeting invites on their IPhone and Outlook client on their PC or laptop. Also, could be where your ActiveSync continues to synch emails and calendar meetings where it continues to send out old and same invite over and over again.

Suggestion(s) that may help fix this.

-	Disable iCloud sync on all of your iDevices, iPhone, iPad, Mac Outlook machine for both calendar and reminders sync that should resolve your issue.
-	From what I understand a workaround is to disable the time to leave feature (TTL) on your device. Settings > Calendar > Default Alert Times > disable Time to Leave.

The above does not guaranteed to work or fix the issue but worth a try. Apple and Microsoft have not gotten any fix for this problem yet.

 For now, the recommendations:
